<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>PICARD:  Red alert. It seems you were right, Mister O'Brien. Ready phasers, load torpedoes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>WORF:  Phasers armed. Loading forward and aft torpedo bays.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  Sir, let me beam over. Try to talk to him. We served together a long time. When you've been through what we have, you tend to get inside someone. He might listen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>RIKER:  He'd never drop his shields and allow you to transport on board.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  The Phoenix is using a high energy sensor system. It cycles every five point five minutes. Between cycles there's a window of a fiftieth of a second. Trust me, I can get through.</td></tr>

