<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  He will. Count on it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>MAXWELL:  What the hell has happened to this war?</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  Sir, there is no war. The war is over.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>MAXWELL:  You're wrong. The Cardassians live to make war.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  That's what everybody thinks about the enemy. That's probably what they think about us.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>MAXWELL:  We're not the same at all. We do not start wars. We do not make surprise attacks on manned outposts. We do not butcher women and children in their homes. Children who never got the chance to grow up. You were with me on Setlick. You saw what they did.</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  Yes, sir.</td></tr>

