<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>O'BRIEN:  (sings) The minstrel boy to the war has gone. In the ranks of death you will find him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>BOTH:  His father's sword he hath girded on and his wild harp slung behind him. Land of song, said the warrior bard, tho' all the world betrays thee. One sword at least thy rights shall guard.</td></tr>

